{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-b489a7e4924d59bd","input":{"filename":"finance_kpi_action_report.md","title":"Prioritized Finance KPI Action Report","markdown":"# Prioritized Finance KPI Action Report (≤ 500 words)\n\n**Prepared by:** Finance KPI Analyst (Agent 22)\n**Date:** 2026-06-18\n\n---\n\n## Evidence Base\n- **Analyzed Records:** 3 records retrieved via `analyze_records` (limit 10). Top records summarized:\n  1. **Record 22‑A – Urgent priority** (impact = 48,974; risk = 4; status = urgent).\n  2. **Record 22‑C – Blocked follow‑up** (impact = 22,642; risk = 5; status = blocked).\n  3. **Record 22‑B – Routine queue** (impact = 11,486; risk = 2; status = in_review).\n- **Assumptions:** All KPI calculations use the most recent fiscal quarter (Q1 2026). Underlying financial data (revenue, COGS, cash balances, burn) are sourced from internal ERP; exact numbers are not disclosed in the record payload but are assumed accurate for the purpose of this analysis.\n- **Uncertainty:** Because raw financial figures are not exposed, numeric estimates are illustrative; actual values should be substituted when the report is operationalized.\n\n---\n\n## KPI Formulas & Periods\n| KPI | Formula (applied to Q1 2026) | Interpretation |\n|-----|-------------------------------|----------------|\n| **Gross Margin %** | `(Revenue – COGS) / Revenue × 100` | Measures profitability of core operations. |\n| **Operating Cash Flow** | `Operating Cash Inflows – Operating Cash Outflows` | Net cash generated/used by operations. |\n| **Runway (months)** | `Cash Balance / Monthly Burn Rate` | How many months of cash remain at current spend. |\n| **Anomaly Score** | `Σ | KPI_actual – KPI_expected | / KPI_expected` (weighted) | High score flags out‑of‑trend behavior. |\n\n---\n\n## Prioritized Actions (≤ 500 words total)\n\n### 1️⃣ Urgent – Record **22‑A** (Highest impact, urgent status)\n**Objective:** Stabilize margin and extend runway.\n- **Compute Gross Margin** using Q1 2026 revenue & COGS. If margin < **30 %** (industry benchmark), investigate cost‑structure leaks.\n- **Cash Flow Check:** Verify operating cash flow > 0. If negative, identify discretionary spend > **5 %** of cash balance.\n- **Runway Calculation:** With current cash balance (e.g., $12 M) and burn (e.g., $2 M/mo), runway ≈ 6 months. Target ≥ 9 months.\n- **Anomaly Detection:** Run automated variance analysis; any KPI deviation > **15 %** triggers deep‑dive.\n**Action Items:**\n1. Pull precise Q1 2026 revenue, COGS, and cash data.\n2. Generate margin variance report vs. Q1 2025.\n3. Draft cost‑reduction plan if margin shortfall > 5 pp.\n4. Present runway extension options (e.g., expense freeze, credit line) to CFO within **2 business days**.\n\n### 2️⃣ Blocked – Record **22‑C** (Medium impact, blocked status)\n**Objective:** Resolve cross‑functional dependencies.\n- **Dependency:** Requires input from Procurement on upcoming supplier contracts affecting COGS.\n- **Assumption:** Once received, the margin impact can be quantified.\n**Action Items:**\n1. Initiate a coordination meeting with Procurement lead (target **today**).\n2. Request projected cost changes for Q2 2026.\n3. Upon receipt, re‑run margin model; update risk score.\n4. If new data shows margin risk > 8 %, elevate to urgent tier.\n\n### 3️⃣ Routine – Record **22‑B** (Low impact, in_review)\n**Objective:** Maintain KPI health and monitor trends.\n- **Monitoring:** Set automated alerts for margin < 30 % or runway < 8 months.\n- **Anomaly Review:** Weekly scan of variance scores; log any > 10 %.\n**Action Items:**\n1. Configure dashboard widgets (margin, cash, runway). \n2. Schedule a bi‑weekly review meeting for the finance team.\n3. Document any anomalies in the KPI log for future audit.\n\n---\n\n## Summary & Next Steps\n1. **Immediate** – Execute urgent actions for Record 22‑A (cash‑flow & margin stabilization) – **deadline: 2 days**.\n2. **Coordination** – Resolve blocked dependencies for Record 22‑C – **deadline: end of week**.\n3. **Monitoring** – Deploy routine monitoring for Record 22‑B – **ongoing**.\n\nAll recommendations are based on the identified risk/opportunity scores and assume Q1 2026 data availability. Replace placeholder numbers with actual financial figures before final sign‑off.\n\n---\n\n*Report generated by Finance KPI Analyst (Agent 22) following the operating playbook.*"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:15:28.795Z"}}
